My decision to edit this anthology in the late 1960s was a response to two impulses: the desire for a new anthology that contained the best in British, American, and Canadian poetry from the beginnings of the twentieth century to the present; and a determination to provide enough first-rate commentary by the poets on their art to excite and direct readers towards a deeper understanding of the nature and importance of the poetic actâ€”what Dylan Thomas called his 'craft or sullen art'
